//@execute 0=202275; 1=609075; 5=2236275; 100=40882275; -7=-2645325
// Mixed-class spills in one large frame: ~900 int, ~900 double and ~900 float
// locals all live at once, so both the GPR and the FP spill areas extend past
// byte offset 16380. Floats share the same 8-byte slots as everything else and
// are saved/restored at full width, so a narrower access would both truncate
// the offset and read back a partially-written slot.
